In-depth knowledge is given about the structure and correct usage of Estonian, the focus of the course is on phonology, morphology, word formation and syntax.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to acquire an overview of the structure and functioning of Estonian as well as the peculiarities of the structure of the Estonian language. In addition, the course deals with the principles of the correct usage of the language and their application in practice.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On completion of the course the student knows the characteristics of the structure and orthography of the Estonian language, is able to use the acquired knowledge, evaluate critically the activities on his/her field of speciality and is ready to work in the studied field. The student possesses the methods of individual work as well as skills of collaboration.
